@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@next "Perf Editor"
@prev "Copyright"
QED is an editor for the Quasar synthesizer and allows you to edit nearly all
parameters of the Quasar on your Amiga.  It is recommended that you are
familar with the Quasar.  This documentation will not explain the meaning of
all parameters. Please refer to your Quasar manual for further details.

QED offers the following features:

  * Support of internal *AND* external modules
  * Realtime editing



To do:

  * Support for external RAM board
@endnode

@node "Perf Editor" "Performance Editor"
@next "GM Editor"
@prev "Introduction"
 @{i}Buttons below of the performance list:@{ui}

 @{b}Load Map@{ub}       
 Load a complete map of 100 performances from disk 

 @{b}Save Map@{ub}
 Save current performance bank to disk

 @{b}Copy@{ub}           
 Copy current performance to clipboard

 @{b}Paste@{ub}  
 Replace current performance by performance from clipboard

 @{b}Update Map@{ub}     
 Update current performance map by refetching all 100
 performances from the Quasar


 @{i}Buttons on the right side:@{ui}

 @{b}Write@{ub}            
 Write performance changes to Quasar internal memory

 @{b}Write to...@{ub}      
 Write performance changes to a different performance

 @{b}Load Perf@{ub}        
 Load a performance from disk

 @{b}Save Perf @{ub}       
 Save current performance to disk

 @{b}Save All@{ub}         
 Load all performances of the current map to 'QED:Perf'


 @{i}Warning:@{ui} Some buttons are disabled when you have selected a ROM
 bank. It makes no sense using @{b}Write@{ub} because you can't change
 any resident performance expect performances of a RAM bank.
 

 If you have AmigaDos 3.0+, @{"click here" link "Pics/PerfEditor.iff/main" 0} for a picture of this window.
@endnode

@node "GM Editor" "General Midi Editor"
@next "FX 1 Editor"
@prev "Perf Editor"
 @{i}Buttons of the right side of the part editor window:@{ui}

 @{b}Send@{ub}          
 Send parameters of all 16 parts to the Quasar
 
 @{b}Update@{ub}        
 Refetch all part parameters from Quasar

 @{b}Load Map@{ub}     
 Load a map of 16 parts from disk and transmit them to the Quasar
 
 @{b}Save Map@{ub}      
 Save current part map to disk

 @{b}Copy@{ub}          
 Copy current part to clipboard

 @{b}Paste@{ub}         
 Replace current part by part from clipboard

 @{b}Test@{ub}          
 Test current part (@{"Test window" link "Test Sound" 0})

 @{b}Change Map@{ub}    
 Switch to @{"Program change editor" link "Program Change Map Editor" 0}

 @{b}Mod Matrix@{ub}    
 Edit @{"modulation matrix" link "Modulation Matrix" 0} for GM Mode


 If you have AmigaDos 3.0+, @{"click here" link "Pics/GMEditor.iff/main" 0} for a picture of this window.
@endnode

@node "FX 1 Editor" "FX 1"
@next "FX 2 Editor"
@prev "GM Editor"
The FX1 editor allows you to edit the FX1 parameters, either for

 - the current performance or 
 - for all GM parts.

Parameters are described in your Quasar manual.


@{b} Send@{ub}       - Send all parameters to the Quasar
@{b} Update@{ub}     - Request FX1 parameters from Quasar
@{b} Load@{ub}       - Load a set of parameters from disk
@{b} Save@{ub}       - Save current parameters to disk


If you have AmigaDos 3.0+, @{"click here" link "Pics/FX1Editor.iff/main" 0} for a picture of this window.
@endnode

@node "FX 2 Editor" "FX 2 Editor"
@next "Drums Editor"
@prev "FX 1 Editor"
The FX2 editor allows you to edit the FX2 parameters, either for

 - the current performance or 
 - for all GM parts.

Parameters are described in your Quasar manual.


@{b} Send@{ub}       - Send all parameters to the Quasar
@{b} Update@{ub}     - Request FX2 parameters from Quasar
@{b} Load@{ub}       - Load a set of parameters from disk
@{b} Save@{ub}       - Save current parameters to disk


 If you have AmigaDos 3.0+, @{"click here" link "Pics/FX2Editor.iff/main" 0} for a picture of this window.
@endnode

@node "Drums Editor" "Drums Editor"
@next "Arpeggiator Editor"
@prev "FX 2 Editor"
The Drums editor allows you to change the parameters of each drum instrument.

Parameters are described in your Quasar manual.

@{b} Send@{ub}       - Send all drum parameters to the Quasar
@{b} Update@{ub}     - Request drum parameters from Quasar
@{b} Load@{ub}       - Load a set of parameters from disk
@{b} Save@{ub}       - Save current parameters to disk

 If you have AmigaDos 3.0+, @{"click here" link "Pics/DrumsEditor.iff/main" 0} for a picture of this window.
@endnode

@node "Part Editor" "Part Editor"
@next "Program Change Map Editor"
@prev "Arpeggiator Editor"
The part editor allows you to edit a part either of a performance or a one of
the 16 GM parts. The part editor consists of six pages:

 @{b}Sounds@{ub}
 displays two lists with the available sound banks and the sounds that 
 are contained in the selected bank. Press the button @{"Select sound" link "Soundlist" 0} to
 open the sound selector window.
        
 @{b}Main Parameters@{ub}
 shows the most important parts of the selected part.

 @{b}Envelope@{ub}
 allows you to edit the envelope of the selected part either with the sliders
 of with the mouse. The envelope is shown in a different window.

 @{b}Vibrato@{ub}
 Vibrato settings of the selected part.

 @{b}Frequencies@{ub}
 Cutoff and resonance settings of the selected part.

 @{b}Miscellaneous@{ub}
 Misccellaneous part settings.

There are also three buttons common to all pages:

 @{b}Reset part@{ub}
 This button will reset all parameters of the selected part to the
 Quasar factory settings.

 @{b}Load part@{ub}
 Load a part from disk and replace the current part.

 @{b}Save part@{ub}
 Save current part to disk.


If you have AmigaDos 3.0+, @{"click here" link "Pics/PartEditor.iff/main" 0} for a picture of this window.
@endnode

@node "Program Change Map Editor" "Program Change Map Editor"
@next "Performance Library"
@prev "Part Editor"
The Program Change Map editor allows you to create your own GM Bank.  In the
normal case the sounds from 0 to 127 are predefined by the GM standard.  If
you want to use sound from another bank you have to use this editor.  The list
on the top side displays all sounds from 0 to 127.  The two lists below show
the bank and the sound that is associated with the sound in the upper list.


 If you have AmigaDos 3.0+, @{"click here" link "Pics/ChangeEditor.iff/main" 0} for a picture of this window.
@endnode

@node "Performance Library" "Performance Library"
@next "QED Settings"
@prev "Program Change Map Editor"
If you have AmigaDos 3.0+, @{"click here" link "Pics/Perflib1.iff/main" 0} for a picture of the Performance Library
in search mode.  

If you have AmigaDos 3.0+, @{"click here" link "Pics/Perflib2.iff/main" 0} for a picture of the Performance Library
in edit mode.
@endnode

@node "Arpeggiator Editor" "Arpeggiator Editor"
@next "Part Editor"
@prev "Drums Editor"
 The arpeggitor editor allows you to edit the arpeggiator  parameters,  
 either for

 - the current performance or  
 - for all GM parts.

 The parameters are described in your Quasar manual.

@{b} Send@{ub}       - Send all parameters to the Quasar
@{b} Update@{ub}     - Request arpeggiator parameters from Quasar
@{b} Load@{ub}       - Load a set of parameters from disk
@{b} Save@{ub}       - Save current parameters to disk

 If you have AmigaDos 3.0+, @{"click here" link "Pics/ArpEditor.iff/main" 0} for a picture of this window.
@endnode

@node "QED Settings" "QED Settings"
@next "Quasar Settings"
@prev "Program Change Map Editor"
 The QED settings window is splitted in three different pages:

 @{u}Page @{b}Misc@{ub}:@{uu}
 
 @{b}Overwrite warnings@{ub}
   pop up a warning requester when you are going to overwrite 
   an existing file
 @{b}Default mode@{ub}
   select the default mode (GM/Performance) when you start QED
 @{b}Guide@{ub}
   path of the QED Amigaguide help file

 @{u}Page @{b}Performances@{ub}:@{uu}

 @{b}Autowrite performances@{ub}
 @{b}Autoget performance map@{ub}
   fetch performance map automatically when you select 
   a new performance bank

 @{u}Page @{b}Internals@{ub}:@{uu}

 @{b}RAM card@{ub}
   Is a RAM card installed ? 
 @{b}ROM card 1@{ub}
   Is a ROM card installed ? 
 @{b}ROM card 2@{ub}
   Is a second ROM card installed ? 
 @{b}Quasar version@{ub}
   Show version of the QED operating system
 @{b}Fetch internal data@{ub}
   Fetch list of single sound names and all internal ROM performances.
   This button must be used after running QED for the first time or
   after changing your Quasar, e.g. after adding or removing a module.

 @{u}Common buttons:@{uu}

 @{b}Load@{ub} 
   Load QED settings from disk
 @{b}Save@{ub}
   Save QED settings to disk
 

 If you have Amiga Dos 3.0+, @{"click here" link "Pics/QEDSettings.iff/main" 0} for a picture of this window.
@endnode

@node "Quasar Settings" "Quasar Settings"
@next "History"
@prev "QED Settings"
The Quasar settings are global.  They are used in the performance and GM mode.
The meaning of the parameters are described in your Quasar user manual. Please
refer to this document if you need more informations.

The MIDI I/O handling is splitted in three pages:

 @{b}Midi Input Handling@{ub}
 @{b}Midi Output Handling@{ub}
 @{b}Global Midi Switches@{ub}

If you have AmigaDos 3.0+, @{"click here" link "Pics/QuasarSettings.iff/main" 0} for a picture of this window.
@endnode

