@node "Environment" "Environment"
@prev "Installer Copyright"
 Used hardware:  - Amiga 2000/A2630/25Mhz 
                 - Kickstart 3.1

 Used software:  - Dice 3.0 Professional
                 - MUI Builder 2.1
                 - MUI 2.3
                 - good old 'sed' streamline editor
                 - Heddley 1.1 for writing this help file

 Test platforms: - Amiga 2000/A2630/25, Kickstart 3.1
                 - Amiga 500/8MHz, Kickstart 2.04
@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
QED requires:

  * Amiga with Kickstart 2.04 or higher
  * at least 1.5 MB Ram
  * Magic User Interface - MUI V 2.3 or higher
  * MIDI interface
  * and of course a Quasar

I strongly suggest to use an accelerated Amiga (>=68020).
@endnode

@node "Menus of QED" "Menus of QED"
The following menus are common to all windows of QED:

 @{b}Project@{ub}
     Load                 Load all QED temporary parameters
     Save                 Save all QED temporary parameters
     About                Show the About requester
     Help                 This help
     Iconify              Iconify QED and free serial port
     Quit                 Leave QED 
 

 @{b}Preferences@{ub}
     QED settings         @{"Change settings of QED" link "QED Settings" 0}
     Quasar settings      @{"Change Quasar settings" link "Quasar Settings" 0}
@endnode

@node "Modulation Matrix" "Modulation Matrix"
Edit the modulation matrix either of the current performance or of the GM
mode.

If you have AmigaDos 3.0+, @{"click here" link "Pics/ModMatrix.iff/main" 0} for a picture of this window.
@endnode

@node "Write Performance" "Write Performance"
This window appears when you press the @{b}Write to...@{ub}  button in the performance
editor. It allows you to write the current performance to custom position in
one of the RAM banks.

If you have AmigaDos 3.0+, @{"click here" link "Pics/WritePerformance.iff/main" 0} for a picture of this window.
@endnode

@node "Soundlist" "Soundlist"
The soundlist window shows all available sound in sorted order.  Initally the
list will contain more than 1000 sounds.  You can enter a pattern to decrease
the number of sounds to be shown.  The @{b}pattern@{ub} "*" affects to show all sounds.
All standard Amiga patterns are allowed. For example you can use "*bass*" to
display all sounds that contain the substring "bass". The @{b}Clear@{ub} button will
resets the pattern gadget to "*".

If you have AmigaDos 3.0+, @{"click here" link "Pics/Soundlist.iff/main" 0} for a picture of this window.
@endnode

@node "Test Sound" "Test Sound"
@{b}Test Sound@{ub} allows to hear the current sound.  So there is no need to use your
master keyboard.

  @{b}Play sound@{ub}        - plays a single note (C-5)
  @{b}Play chord@{ub}        - plays a C maj chord 
  @{b}Play melody@{ub}       - plays a little melody (currently not implemented)


If you have AmigaDos 3.0+, @{"click here" link "Pics/TestSound.iff/main" 0} for a picture of this window.
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"
You must have the @{"Installer" link "Installer Copyright" 0} script to perform a proper installation.  No
warranty is given for a self-made installation.  Use the @{b}Help@{ub} button of the
Installer program to get some additional help.
@endnode

